tags: So what happens at the end here
I believe ultimately Dumbledore and Snape
The sixth book touches on it the most
As does the story of the Deathly Hallows
Truly ancient powerful wizarding magic essentially
I don't think Harry even really represents the magical world super well even per se
Ultimately he's another student at Hogwarts
Grindedlwald and all of them are
Such as shown in the fantastic beast series
And it's really just a quirk of their larger scale battles
That Harry ends up with the elder wand and all of that
I think he would just store it away basically
And hope that the Powerful ancient houses of Slytherin and Gryffindor
Continue to define themselves on their own terms
And ascend as the unique potent things that they are

body:
reunion

dobby looked down at his stomach. there was a hole where a wound had been but there was no blood. his clothes were cleaner than they had been a few minutes ago, and he felt different—lighter.

he looked around, trying to make sense of the images surrounding where he stood. he walked forward and saw people ahead of him, so he kept walking.

after months of dobby living in this strange place he had learned to accept the comfortable conditions of, he had an unlikely encounter. walking down the alley he noticed a young boy with bright green eyes and a lightning scar.

“harry potter?”

the boy turned around and met dobby’s giant, protruding eyes.

“dobby! what are you doing here? where am i?”

“i’m not sure, sir! but it’s so good to see you! i wonder if you might come with me! i have made a home here and have met some very good friends who would be as honored as i was to meet you!”

“dobby, that would be amazing, but unfortunately i have somewhere to be.”

“oh! where are you going, sir?”

“on,” harry said, and dobby didn’t see harry potter for a very long time, until one day he returned but looked different—his scar was more faded and his face was older but his eyes were still as green. dobby recognized him immediately.

summary: Prompt: Merope Gaunt was not a witch, she was a demon - specifically a cat demon. As a half demon, Tom has superior senses,...
body: Prompt: Merope Gaunt was not a witch, she was a demon - specifically a cat demon. As a half demon, Tom has superior senses, strength and agility compared to a human or wizard. He also has cat ears, and several cattish behaviours which he can’t really help or hide. Harry on the other hand comes from a family of crow demons. Naturally, they are worst enemies.
